1
00:00:06,816 --> 00:00:08,715
Dean, have you got a moment?
Dean, 你有空吗?

2
00:00:08,716 --> 00:00:10,487
Sure. I'm on my way home.
有的. 我在回家的路上.

3
00:00:10,795 --> 00:00:14,270
I'm working on a scheme to attract younger customers.
我正在做一个方案 来吸引年轻的顾客.

4
00:00:14,271 --> 00:00:15,192
To the restaurant?
(吸引)到餐厅?

5
00:00:15,193 --> 00:00:16,389
Yes.
是的

6
00:00:16,955 --> 00:00:20,512
"Youth Market Trends in the Dining Industry".
"年轻人的市场发展趋势  在餐饮业"

7
00:00:20,727 --> 00:00:22,191
I beg your pardon?
请再说一遍?

8
00:00:22,239 --> 00:00:25,187
My research last semester was on this topic.
我上一学期的研究  就是这个话题.

9
00:00:25,188 --> 00:00:26,635
Do go on.
继续说.

10
00:00:26,716 --> 00:00:31,556
Well, in general, younger customers prefer casual dining.
Well, 总的来说, 年轻的顾客更喜欢休闲的进餐.

11
00:00:31,557 --> 00:00:32,631
Yes.
是的.

12
00:00:32,632 --> 00:00:34,523
They like finger food.
他们喜欢手指食物(finger food).

13
00:00:34,524 --> 00:00:37,965
In fact, they often order appetizers.
事实上, 他们经常会点开胃菜(appetizers)

14
00:00:37,966 --> 00:00:41,750
In the bar, they prefer beer and wine to hard liquor.
在酒吧, 他们喜欢啤酒和红酒胜过烈性酒.

15
00:00:41,751 --> 00:00:43,885
Is that information useful?
那信息有用吗?

16
00:00:43,886 --> 00:00:46,935
Absolutely. Let me ask you a question.
绝对地. 让我问你一个问题.

17
00:00:48,608 --> 00:00:50,782
Do they prefer large portions?
他们喜欢更大的分量吗?

18
00:00:50,783 --> 00:00:52,958
I mean, is that important?
我的意思是, 那重要吗?

19
00:00:52,959 --> 00:00:55,306
Sure. They like large portions,
是的. 他们喜欢更大的分量,

20
00:00:55,307 --> 00:00:57,829
but they prefer lower prices.
但是他们更喜欢便宜的价格.

21
00:00:57,830 --> 00:01:00,760
After all, they're not making much money yet!
毕竟, 他们还赚不了多少钱!

22
00:01:00,889 --> 00:01:02,852
Is that the voice of experience, Dean?
那是经验之谈吗, Dean?

23
00:01:02,853 --> 00:01:05,117
Highly researched, of course.
深入地调查后的(结论), 当然了.

